# G-DG-STREAMFIX - DiffusionGemma native forward: streaming-weight DEADLOCK fixed + 5/5 reliability
# date: 2026-06-21
# sp_status: GREEN. The diffusion_gemma_forward_cuda mid-forward deadlock (G-DIFFJUDGE-NATIVE.log)
#            is FIXED. test_diffgemma_forward.exe (G_DG_N1B) ran 5/5 consecutive times to full
#            completion, every run checks=7 fails=0, 256/256 canvas logits finite + in-vocab.
# repro: build -> (vcvars64.bat) ; cd build-cuda ; ninja test_diffgemma_forward
#        run  -> build-cuda\tests\test_diffgemma_forward.exe   (5x in a row)
#        model env defaults C:\sp_models\diffusiongemma-26B-A4B.{sp-model,sp-tokenizer}
# ===================================================================================================
# == ROOT CAUSE (confirmed) ==
#   The 26B-A4B OK_Q4B model is 14 GB. Its arena packed-weight buffers (sp_frob_packed_tensor:
#   codes / row_scale / row_prec / bscale) ALIAS the read-only MapViewOfFile view of the .sp-model
#   (sp_model_load.c map_file -> MapViewOfFile; "arena tensors alias mmap"). The diffusion forward
#   streams per-layer expert weights by dequanting those aliased pointers DURING compute
#   (dg_upload_arena_rows/_w -> sp_arena_dequant_row -> reads t->codes+row_off[r] / t->bscale).
#   On this memory-constrained box (12 GB GPU, limited RAM/commit; N0 OOM'd, pagefile system-managed)
#   the per-layer demand page-fault on the mmap view under commit pressure DEADLOCKS (CPU ~0% /
#   GPU 0% / disk idle / WorkingSet pinned ~99 MB), nondeterministically at L5/L12/L14 (a page-cache
#   boundary). A full sequential pre-warm read (14.2 GB in 6.7 s) did NOT fix it and the OS did not
#   retain the pages -> the hang is the MapViewOfFile demand-fault path, not cold-read latency.
#
# == FIX (Option A spirit: explicit resident read; diffusion-path / arch_id 9 ONLY, additive) ==
#   New static helper dg_dequant_resident_rows() in src/backends/cuda/cuda_forward.cu: before
#   dequant, COPY the exact aliased source byte-ranges for the rows about to be read (codes slice
#   [row_off[r0] .. row_off[last]+last_len), plus per-row row_prec/row_scale/bscale slices) into
#   OWNED, committed heap buffers, build a local sp_frob_packed_tensor over the copies, and dequant
#   from THAT via sp_arena_dequant_row (identical arithmetic, byte-for-byte). The memcpy forces every
#   source page resident SYNCHRONOUSLY (no demand fault during the dequant loop), and the owned buffer
#   is reclaimable HEAP -- not a reclaimable file-cache page -- so it cannot be trimmed mid-read.
#   Resident host memory is bounded to ~one tensor slice (freed per call) -> peak WorkingSet now
#   ~3.3 GB (bounded), NOT the 14 GB demand-paged thrash. dg_upload_arena_w, dg_upload_arena_rows, and
#   the per-token embedding gather all route through it. Dense gemma4/gemma3/qwen3 + 12B paths never
#   call it (no other sp_arena_dequant_row site changed) -> byte-identical. No ABI / .sp-model change.
#
# diff: src/backends/cuda/cuda_forward.cu  (additive, diffusion-path only):
#       + static int dg_dequant_resident_rows(const sp_arena_tensor*, int r0, int rows, float* dst)
#       ~ dg_upload_arena_w / dg_upload_arena_rows: dequant via the resident snapshot
#       ~ embedding gather loop: dg_dequant_resident_rows(eat, tokens[t], 1, ...) per token
#       (0 deletions to any non-diffusion path; no math-core / submodule edit needed.)
# build: ninja test_diffgemma_forward -> cuda_forward.cu compiled clean (only pre-existing unrelated
#        warning #550-D at line 4081), [3/3] Linking tests\test_diffgemma_forward.exe -> OK.
# ===================================================================================================
